                            <comment id="12868482" author="tlipcon" created="Tue, 18 May 2010 01:39:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that gets the stuff working for me again. I havent tried actually doing a tarball build/deploy after these changes, though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12868519" author="stack" created="Tue, 18 May 2010 04:12:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.  Thanks Todd.  Added a MAVEN_HOME handling in case mvn is elsewhere, not on the path.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12868522" author="stack" created="Tue, 18 May 2010 04:20:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I changed the wiki removing the bit about building classpath using maven dependency plugin to run hbase in-situ.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12868948" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 19 May 2010 01:26:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a typo in /tmp/hbase-core-tets-classpath.txt, also we should probably print something when it&apos;s fetching jars (I thought it was stuck until Todd explained to me that maven was doing a full web crawl for fun).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12868976" author="stack" created="Wed, 19 May 2010 03:43:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed spelling mistake.  It did not hamper functionality.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017337" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:42:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
